WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.860
The Cup in the Forest by Anne Collins Penguin Active Reading Easy Start

00:07.860 --> 00:16.900
Pear and his girlfriend Nina live in a big town in Norway.

00:16.900 --> 00:21.340
They are on holiday in the country.

00:21.340 --> 00:26.020
They are driving on a road near a big forest.

00:27.020 --> 00:31.020
It's beautiful here, Pear says.

00:31.020 --> 00:37.020
Let's stop the car and walk in the forest.

00:37.020 --> 00:42.020
But the forest is very dark and quiet.

00:42.020 --> 00:47.020
I don't like this place, Nina says.

00:47.020 --> 00:49.020
I'm cold.

00:49.020 --> 00:53.020
Let's go back to the car.

00:54.020 --> 00:58.020
Suddenly, Pear falls over a tree.

00:58.020 --> 01:03.020
Are you okay, Nina asks?

01:03.020 --> 01:06.020
Yes, Pear answers.

01:06.020 --> 01:11.020
Then he sees some old stones.

01:11.020 --> 01:16.020
These are very strange stones, he says.

01:16.020 --> 01:19.020
He moves them with his hands.

01:19.020 --> 01:23.020
They are very heavy.

01:23.020 --> 01:28.020
There's a hole under the stones, he says.

01:28.020 --> 01:31.020
He puts his hand into the hole.

01:31.020 --> 01:35.020
Be careful, Nina says.

01:35.020 --> 01:40.020
Perhaps an animal lives in there.

01:40.020 --> 01:43.020
Pear takes his hand from the hole.

01:43.020 --> 01:48.020
He has an old cup in his hand.

01:48.020 --> 01:52.020
Look at this old cup, Nina, he says.

01:52.020 --> 01:55.020
It's very interesting.

01:55.020 --> 01:58.020
But why is it here?

01:58.020 --> 02:04.020
And look, there are some strange words on it.

02:04.020 --> 02:07.020
Nina looks at the cup too.

02:07.020 --> 02:11.020
It's beautiful, she says.

02:11.020 --> 02:17.020
She looks again and very expensive, she thinks.

02:18.020 --> 02:23.020
The forest is very dark and cold.

02:23.020 --> 02:26.020
Let's go now, Nina says.

02:26.020 --> 02:30.020
I don't like this forest.

02:30.020 --> 02:33.020
They walk back to their car.

02:33.020 --> 02:37.020
Suddenly, Pear stops.

02:37.020 --> 02:41.020
What is it? Nina asks.

02:41.020 --> 02:44.020
Pear looks into the trees.

02:44.020 --> 02:48.020
There's a man there, he says.

02:48.020 --> 02:51.020
Nina looks too.

02:51.020 --> 02:55.020
I can't see a man, she says.

02:55.020 --> 02:58.020
Pear looks again.

02:58.020 --> 03:01.020
You're right, he says.

03:01.020 --> 03:04.020
It's only a tree.

03:04.020 --> 03:09.020
Pear and Nina drive to a small town.

03:09.020 --> 03:12.020
It's getting dark, Pear says.

03:12.020 --> 03:15.020
Let's stay in this town.

03:15.020 --> 03:18.020
They find a small hotel.

03:18.020 --> 03:22.020
The people are very friendly.

03:22.020 --> 03:25.020
I like this hotel, Nina says.

03:25.020 --> 03:28.020
Let's stay here.

03:28.020 --> 03:33.020
Near the hotel is a museum.

03:33.020 --> 03:39.020
We can take the cup to the museum in the morning, Pear says.

03:39.020 --> 03:45.020
We can ask the curator about it.

03:45.020 --> 03:49.020
Later, Pear can't sleep.

03:49.020 --> 03:56.020
He goes to the window of his room and looks into the hotel garden.

03:56.020 --> 03:59.020
A strange man is standing there.

03:59.020 --> 04:02.020
He doesn't move.

04:02.020 --> 04:06.020
Who are you, Pear calls?

04:06.020 --> 04:09.020
What do you want?

04:09.020 --> 04:13.020
Then Nina comes into the room.

04:13.020 --> 04:18.020
There's a strange man in the garden, Pear says.

04:18.020 --> 04:22.020
What man? Nina asks.

04:22.020 --> 04:26.020
I can't see a man.

04:26.020 --> 04:32.020
In the morning, Pear and Nina take the cup to the museum.

04:32.020 --> 04:37.020
The museum curator is an old man.

04:37.020 --> 04:42.020
Do you know about this cup, Pear asks?

04:42.020 --> 04:48.020
The curator looks at the cup for a long time.

04:48.020 --> 04:53.020
Where is it from, he asks.

04:53.020 --> 05:00.020
From a hole under some old stones in the forest, Pear says.

05:00.020 --> 05:04.020
Take the cup back to the forest.

05:04.020 --> 05:09.020
Now the curator says.

05:09.020 --> 05:14.020
But why, Pear asks?

05:14.020 --> 05:17.020
Do you see the old words on the cup?

05:17.020 --> 05:20.020
The curator asks.

05:20.020 --> 05:26.020
They say, this cup belongs to Harkon.

05:26.020 --> 05:29.020
Be careful.

05:29.020 --> 05:34.020
Who is Harkon, Pear asks?

05:34.020 --> 05:40.020
Harkon is an old Viking name, the curator says.

05:40.020 --> 05:44.020
There are some Viking graves in the forest.

05:44.020 --> 05:48.020
This cup is from Harkon's grave.

05:48.020 --> 05:54.020
Take it back there. Now.

05:54.020 --> 06:00.020
Pear and Nina are drinking coffee in the hotel.

06:00.020 --> 06:05.020
Let's take the cup back to the forest, Pear says.

06:05.020 --> 06:09.020
Are you crazy? Nina says.

06:09.020 --> 06:13.020
Why do you listen to the old man's stories?

06:13.020 --> 06:17.020
Harkon is only a dead Viking.

06:17.020 --> 06:20.020
Yes, Pear says.

06:20.020 --> 06:26.020
But I'm afraid. The cup belongs to him.

06:26.020 --> 06:32.020
Suddenly, Pear sees the strange man across the room.

06:32.020 --> 06:40.020
Look, he says. Harkon is here. He's in this cafe.

06:40.020 --> 06:46.020
Pear runs across the room, but Harkon isn't there.

06:46.020 --> 06:50.020
Then Pear goes back to the table.

06:50.020 --> 06:53.020
But Nina isn't there.

06:53.020 --> 06:57.020
And the bag with the cup isn't there.

06:57.020 --> 07:03.020
He runs to the door of the hotel. He sees Nina in the car.

07:03.020 --> 07:09.020
She is driving away from the hotel very fast.

07:09.020 --> 07:12.020
Stop Nina, Pear calls.

07:12.020 --> 07:15.020
Where are you going?

07:15.020 --> 07:22.020
But Nina doesn't stop. She is driving away with the cup.

07:22.020 --> 07:30.020
Nina drives away from the town. She is driving fast, very fast.

07:30.020 --> 07:37.020
But she isn't afraid. She is thinking about money.

07:37.020 --> 07:41.020
Money is important to Nina.

07:41.020 --> 07:45.020
The cup is in a bag near her.

07:45.020 --> 07:49.020
Nina looks at it and smiles.

07:49.020 --> 07:53.020
Pear is crazy, she thinks.

07:53.020 --> 07:59.020
He's afraid of old stories about dead Vikings.

07:59.020 --> 08:08.020
But the cup belongs to me now. I'm taking it to Oslo. I can sell it there.

08:08.020 --> 08:14.020
Pear runs to the museum and finds the old curator.

08:14.020 --> 08:18.020
Where's the cup? The curator asks.

08:18.020 --> 08:23.020
My girlfriend has it now, Pear answers.

08:23.020 --> 08:30.020
That's bad, the curator says. The cup belongs to Harkon.

08:30.020 --> 08:34.020
But Harkon is dead, Pear says.

08:34.020 --> 08:42.020
Yes, the curator says. But there are strange stories about Viking ghosts.

08:42.020 --> 08:48.020
Take my car and go after your girlfriend.

08:48.020 --> 08:55.020
Nina drives for a long time. It is getting dark.

08:55.020 --> 09:03.020
There are no cars on the road. She can't see any towns or houses or people.

09:03.020 --> 09:11.020
Only forests. Dark, black, forests.

09:11.020 --> 09:17.020
But Nina thinks about money again and she is happy.

09:17.020 --> 09:21.020
Now it is raining.

09:21.020 --> 09:28.020
Suddenly Nina sees a strange man. He is standing on the road.

09:28.020 --> 09:34.020
He is looking at Nina. His face is dark and angry.

09:34.020 --> 09:40.020
Nina screams and screams. She is very afraid.

09:40.020 --> 09:45.020
She can't stop the car and she can't see the road.

09:45.020 --> 09:53.020
She only sees the man's angry face. His eyes are cold and strange.

09:53.020 --> 09:58.020
They are the eyes of a dead man.

09:58.020 --> 10:06.020
The car leaves the road and hits a tree. Then it falls into a river.

10:06.020 --> 10:13.020
The water closes over the car. It is very quiet.

10:13.020 --> 10:22.020
The car, Nina and the cup are in the river.

10:22.020 --> 10:27.020
Later the police come and take the car from the river.

10:27.020 --> 10:31.020
A policeman looks into the car.

10:31.020 --> 10:37.020
There's a girl in here, he says. She's dead.

10:37.020 --> 10:44.020
Pear is there too. He is very unhappy about Nina.

10:44.020 --> 10:48.020
Suddenly he sees a man.

10:48.020 --> 10:53.020
The man is walking into the forest.

10:53.020 --> 11:00.020
The ghost of Harkon. Pear thinks. He is very afraid.

11:00.020 --> 11:07.020
But Harkon is walking away now. He has his cup.

